        <mxCell id="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-14" value="&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(230, 230, 230);&quot;&gt;1.0&lt;/font&gt;" style="whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=#FFF2CC99;" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="790" y="5.5" width="33" height="14.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-19" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;A point (`x_i, y_i`) in image space maps to a line `c=-mx_i+y_i` in (`m, c`) parameter space. A line in image&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;space (with same `m, c`) maps to a point in parameter space.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;This duality allows voting: each image point&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;votes for all possible lines on it, and intersections in parameter space on lines&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;in image space.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#564260;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="48.5" y="383" width="731" height="63" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-13" value="" style="group" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1" connectable="0">
          <mxGeometry x="19" y="304" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-14" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Explain the duality between &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 204);&quot;&gt;image space&lt;/font&gt; and &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 204);&quot;&gt;parameter space&lt;/font&gt; in the Hough transform for line detection using the (`m, c`) parameterization. How does a point in image space map to parameter space, and vice versa?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" parent="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-13" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-15" value="2" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" parent="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-13" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-0" value="" style="group" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1" connectable="0">
          <mxGeometry x="19" y="473" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-1" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Why is the (`\rho, \theta`) parameterization preferred over (`m, c`) for the Hough transform? What are the ranges of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Lexend; font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;`\rho` and `\theta`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-0" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-2" value="3" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-0" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-3" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;(`m, c`) cannot represent vertical lines (`m=\infty`) and can&#39;t accumulate arrays. (`\rho, \infty`) has&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;finite ranges (`0\le\theta&amp;lt;\pi`), (`\rho` bounded by image diagonal), but now can represent all lines including vertical lines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#582826;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="48.5" y="553" width="731" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" value="" style="group" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1" connectable="0">
          <mxGeometry x="49" y="164" width="730" height="114.11000000000001" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-0" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(26, 26, 26);&quot;&gt;based on &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(204, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;first derivative&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(26, 26, 26);&quot;&gt;, makes the contour behave like a &lt;i&gt;rubber band&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D5E8D4;strokeColor=#36393d;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="89.88999999999999" y="50" width="640.11" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-1" value="&lt;font&gt;`E_{\text{elastic}}`&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D4E1F5;strokeColor=#3D506C;container=0;fontStyle=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Fustat;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry y="50" width="90" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-2" value="&lt;font&gt;`E_{\text{smooth}}`&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D4E1F5;strokeColor=#3D506C;container=0;fontStyle=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Fustat;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry y="71.37" width="90" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-5" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;based on &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(204, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;second derivative&lt;/font&gt;, avoid sharp bends, making the contour&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;smooth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D5E8D4;strokeColor=#36393d;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="89.88999999999999" y="71.37" width="640.11" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-8" value="&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Energy Terms&lt;/span&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#7EA6E0;strokeColor=#3D506C;fontColor=#ffffff;container=0;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Fustat;fontStyle=0" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry width="90" height="28.63" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-9" value="&lt;font&gt;`E_{\text{image}}`&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D4E1F5;strokeColor=#3D506C;container=0;fontStyle=1;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Fustat;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry y="28.629999999999995" width="90" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-10" value="Meaning" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#4C7E74;strokeColor=#005700;fontColor=#ffffff;container=0;fontSize=12;fontFamily=Fustat;fontStyle=1" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="89.88999999999999" width="640.11" height="28.63" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-11" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(26, 26, 26);&quot;&gt;attracts contour to strong edges.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D5E8D4;strokeColor=#36393d;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="89.88999999999999" y="28.629999999999995" width="640.11" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mN6tJCPcnrja-PPMutif-12" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;`E_\text{total} = E_{\text{image}} + \alpha E_{\text{elastic}} + \beta E_{\text{smooth}}`&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D5E8D4;strokeColor=#36393d;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=center;gradientColor=#D4E1F5;gradientDirection=west;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#0000CC;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry y="92.74000000000001" width="730" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-5" value="" style="group" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1" connectable="0">
          <mxGeometry x="19" y="623" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-6" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Describe the voting process in the Hough transform for detecting circles of known radius. What does a peak in the accumulator represent?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-5" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-7" value="4" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-5" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-8" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;For each edge point (`x_i, y_i`) vote for all possible centers (`a,b`) such that `(x_i-a)^2+(y_i-b)^2=r^2`, After voting a peak of 2d accumulator array specify the center of circle that passes of many edge points.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#564260;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="50.5" y="703" width="731" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-9" value="" style="group" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1" connectable="0">
          <mxGeometry x="19" y="773" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-10" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;How does knowing the edge direction `\phi`&amp;nbsp; reduce computational cost in circle detection? Why is this an example of a trade-off between image-space work and parameter-space work?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-9" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-11" value="5" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-9" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-12" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;With edge direction `\phi`, the center must be a line perpendicular to the edge at distance `r`&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;This gives &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(204, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;only `2` possible centers&lt;/font&gt; per edge point instead of many centers, so we no longer need to vote more than `2` points, the trade-off is &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(204, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;compute edge direction to reduce parameter space voting&lt;/font&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#582826;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="48" y="853" width="731" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-13" value="" style="group" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1" connectable="0">
          <mxGeometry x="19" y="921" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-14" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Explain the structure and purpose of the `\phi`-table in the Generalized Hough Transform. How is it created, and how is it used during detection?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-13" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-15" value="6" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-13" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-16" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;The `\phi`-table is an offline model of the target shape, for each edge direction the table store vectors `\vec{r}` to reference point. During detection, retrieve point direction then voting to indicate peak reference point.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#564260;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="48" y="1001" width="731" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-17" value="" style="group" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1" connectable="0">
          <mxGeometry x="19" y="1180" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-18" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;What happens to the Generalized Hough Transform when unknown scale and rotation are added? Why does this become impractical?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-17" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-19" value="7" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-17" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-20" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;The accumulator array becomes `4D` - (`x_c, y_c, \text{scale}, \text{rotation}`), for edge point voting also for scale and rotation, this needs large memory and computation.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#582826;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="48" y="1250" width="731" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-21" value="" style="group" parent="eUIRvmHIikGdS-Din99n-1" vertex="1" connectable="0">
          <mxGeometry x="19" y="1320" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-22" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Compare between the Hough transform and active contours (snakes) for boundary detection. What types of problems is each best suited for?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" parent="micHKPwZlRHeAgdPmT2d-21" vertex="1">
