        <mxCell id="2VT8IgdAOZ9plX4UFobo-9" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;Canny uses the gradient operator to &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(204, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;compute magnitude and orientation&lt;/font&gt;, t&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;hen it &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(204, 0, 0), rgb(0, 0, 0));&quot;&gt;applies a 1D Laplacian&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; with gradient direction to find&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;zero-crossings . This combination get &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(204, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;better&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;edge detection with good localization&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#F8CECC;strokeColor=#582826;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;" vertex="1" parent="1">
