        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-22" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(26, 26, 26);&quot;&gt;attracts contour to strong edges.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D5E8D4;strokeColor=#36393d;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-14">
          <mxGeometry x="89.88999999999999" y="28.629999999999995" width="640.11" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-23" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;`E_\text{total} = E_{\text{image}} + \alpha E_{\text{elastic}} + \beta E_{\text{smooth}}`&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#D5E8D4;strokeColor=#36393d;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=center;gradientColor=#D4E1F5;gradientDirection=west;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#0000CC;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-14">
          <mxGeometry y="92.74000000000001" width="730" height="21.37" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-24" value="" style="group" vertex="1" connectable="0" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="21" y="3680" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-25" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Describe the voting process in the Hough transform for detecting circles of known radius. What does a peak in the accumulator represent?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-24">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-26" value="4" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-24">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-27" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;For each edge point (`x_i, y_i`) vote for all possible centers (`a,b`) such that `(x_i-a)^2+(y_i-b)^2=r^2`, After voting a peak of 2d accumulator array specify the center of circle that passes of many edge points.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#564260;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="52.5" y="3760" width="731" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-28" value="" style="group" vertex="1" connectable="0" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="21" y="3830" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-29" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;How does knowing the edge direction `\phi`&amp;nbsp; reduce computational cost in circle detection? Why is this an example of a trade-off between image-space work and parameter-space work?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-28">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-30" value="5" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-28">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-31" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;With edge direction `\phi`, the center must be a line perpendicular to the edge at distance `r`&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;This gives &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(204, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;only `2` possible centers&lt;/font&gt; per edge point instead of many centers, so we no longer need to vote more than `2` points, the trade-off is &lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(204, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;compute edge direction to reduce parameter space voting&lt;/font&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#582826;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="50" y="3910" width="731" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-32" value="" style="group" vertex="1" connectable="0" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="21" y="3978" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-33" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;Explain the structure and purpose of the `\phi`-table in the Generalized Hough Transform. How is it created, and how is it used during detection?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-32">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-34" value="6" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-32">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-35" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;The `\phi`-table is an offline model of the target shape, for each edge direction the table store vectors `\vec{r}` to reference point. During detection, retrieve point direction then voting to indicate peak reference point.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#e1d5e7;strokeColor=#564260;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="50" y="4058" width="731" height="50" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-36" value="" style="group" vertex="1" connectable="0" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="19" y="4130" width="790" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-37" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 110%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Lexend&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;What happens to the Generalized Hough Transform when unknown scale and rotation are added? Why does this become impractical?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=22;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;strokeWidth=1;fontFamily=Mina;arcSize=5;hachureGap=4;align=left;spacingRight=5;fontStyle=0;fillStyle=hachure;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=29;spacingBottom=0;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;fontColor=#333333;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-36">
          <mxGeometry x="26.61" width="763.39" height="55" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-38" value="7" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;strokeWidth=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;fontFamily=Mina;fontStyle=1;fontSize=20;spacingTop=3;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;fillStyle=hachure;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=0;spacingBottom=3;arcSize=14;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DADLaM%2BDisplay;" vertex="1" parent="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-36">
          <mxGeometry width="55.5" height="55.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ucWEhtidr9BQ_HSIXQms-39" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 140%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;The accumulator array becomes `4D` - (`x_c, y_c, \text{scale}, \text{rotation}`), for edge point voting also for scale and rotation, this needs large memory and computation.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;strokeWidth=0.5;fillColor=#FFF2CC;strokeColor=#582826;container=0;fontSize=11;fontStyle=0;fontFamily=Fustat;spacingLeft=2;align=left;spacingTop=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
